Title: Geberit FlowFit 620.124.00.1 Reducing tee 40 x 32 x 40mm
Description: Part of a comprehensive system, this Geberit FlowFit 40 x 32 x 40mm reducing tee is made of polyphenylsulfone (PPSU) and fitted with press-fit connections. Developed with the input of the plumbers who will use it, the innovative FlowFit system ensures always-right installation, for a simpler job on-site with no need for deburring and calibration when cutting to length and the ability to laterally press and rotate for convenient and reliable pressing in difficult spots with no risk of contortion. This system is compatible with both cold and hot potable water, cooling and heating water with or without antifreeze agent and with service water and process water. It can also be used in treated water, rainwater with a pH value of <gt/>6, seawater and extinguishing water (wet, wet/dry or dry). It is also suitable for chemicals and technical liquids, compressed air (oil purity class 0–3), inert gases such as nitrogen and in negative pressure. FlowFit is suitable for a variety of applications, including technical build

Approvals: UK Reg4 approved for drinking waterEnvironmental Product Declaration in accordance with EN 15804 + A2 + AC & ISO 14025 / ISO 21975
